<subSubSection id="C34A652EFFAB5A1AFF2AE98AFE3BFAEC" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AE98AFBE4FD8F" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFF2AE98AFE9EFE7B" bold="true" box="[199,337,438,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Description</emphasis>
. Head. Face (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFE00E98AFDFEFE7B" box="[493,561,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFDCFE98BFDFEFE7B" box="[546,561,439,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with only slightly exposed on lower ½ in lateral view, sparse black and short setae dorsally; remaining area and oral border with abundant long macrosetae directed anteriorly and ventrally (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFF72E9C2FF2CFDA3" box="[159,227,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFF39E9C3FF2CFDA3" box="[212,227,511,535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Postpedicel of antenna as long as scape and pedicel combined (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFC29E9C2FBC5FDA3" box="[964,1034,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFC14E9C3FBC5FDA3" box="[1017,1034,511,535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); scape 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFB88E9C2FB47FDA3" box="[1125,1160,510,535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as pedicel (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFF72EA1EFF2AFD8F" box="[159,229,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFF39EA1FFF2AFD8F" box="[212,229,547,571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); stylus slightly longer than scape and pedicel; apex of stylus bare (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFC34EA1EFBD1FD8F" box="[985,1054,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFBE0EA1FFBD1FD8F" box="[1037,1054,547,571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AEA7AFB41FD12" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Thorax. Tumid, postsutural dorsocentral macrosetae, notopleural, supraalar and postalar macrosetae strong; anatergal setae absent; scutellum tumid as the thorax and coxae, without rim on posterior border; 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFACEEA57FAFEFD37" box="[1315,1329,619,643]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
scutellar macrosetae on posterior border, sparse, fine, short setae on disc and border; pleura asetose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AEA8EFD73FD46" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Wing (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFEFEEA8EFE99FD7F" box="[275,342,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFEABEA8EFE99FD7F" box="[326,342,690,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Cell r 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFE40EA8FFE77FD7F" box="[429,440,691,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
closed before wing margin; stump vein supernumerary crossvein on R 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFB26EAFDFB1CFD7B" box="[1227,1235,705,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
absent; R 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFAAFEAFDFA85FD7B" box="[1346,1354,705,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
ending before the wing tip, and R 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFE56EAD4FE0CFD42" box="[443,451,744,758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="5.0">5</number>
, after; m 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFDC6EAE6FDF8FD46" box="[555,567,730,754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
cell closed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AEB3DFF29FC89" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Legs (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFEE0EB3CFE80FCAC" box="[269,335,768,793]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFEAFEB3CFE80FCAC" box="[322,335,768,792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Coxae gray; femora shining black; tibiae yellow, except for brown stripe anteriorly; tarsus light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AEB74FCABFCD4" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" box="[199,868,840,865]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Abdomen. Vestiture as in notum; sides of all tergites setose.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AEB50FC18FB7C" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Male terminalia. Angled 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFE05EB50FDCBFC31" box="[488,516,876,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="45.0">45</number>
º with abdomen (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFD26EB50FCC0FC31" box="[715,783,876,901]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFCEFEB51FCC0FC31" box="[770,783,877,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); epandrium flat ventrally, looks like goat hoof (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFAABEB50FA42FC31" box="[1350,1421,876,901]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFA90EB51FA42FC31" box="[1405,1421,877,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandria broad and thick, subglobular on proximal 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFD31EBACFD26FC1C" box="[732,745,912,936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFD1EEBACFCCDFC1C" box="[755,770,912,936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
, attenuated distally and meeting in an acute tip (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFACFEBACFA42FC1C" box="[1314,1421,912,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFA8FEBACFA42FC1C" box="[1378,1421,912,937]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">
6 
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFA82EBACFAB2FC1D" bold="true" box="[1391,1405,912,937]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">–</emphasis>
8
</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites globular on basal 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFDE8EB89FDDDFC79" box="[517,530,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFDF6EB89FDE5FC79" box="[539,554,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
, distal 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFD6EEB89FD42FC79" box="[643,653,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFD7AEB89FD68FC79" box="[663,679,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
flattened, elongate, with 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFC38EB89FC31FC79" box="[981,1022,948,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">
3 
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFC0EEB88FC3EFC79" bold="true" box="[995,1009,948,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">–</emphasis>
5
</number>
teeth or spines ventrally (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFADBEB88FA41FC79" box="[1334,1422,948,973]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFA82EB89FA41FC79" box="[1391,1422,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Median region of gonocoxite with round tumid protuberance with few short setae (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFBDBEBE4FB03FC44" box="[1078,1228,984,1009]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 7, 8, 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFB40EBE4FB03FC44" box="[1197,1228,984,1008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite with 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFF7AEBC1FF6AFBA1" box="[151,165,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
conspicuous patches of long setae, 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFDDFEBC1FD8FFBA1" box="[562,576,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
of scattered long, fine, yellow setae directed posteriorly and other with patch of dense long, golden setae directed to opposite side and crossing over hypandrium tip as golden belt (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFAC4EC1CFF7BFBE9" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 7, 8, 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFF7AEC79FF7BFBE9" box="[151,180,1093,1117]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); gonostylus long, flattened towards apex, with abundant short, fine setae and few macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFAEFEC78FA41FBE9" box="[1282,1422,1092,1117]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Figs. 11, 12</figureCitation>
); gonostylus hidden in closed genitalia; hypandrium subglobose and subtriangular, with 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFB88EC54FBBCFB34" box="[1125,1139,1128,1152]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
small tubercles on tip and patch of 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFF16ECB1FED8FB11" box="[251,279,1165,1189]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="12.0">12</number>
long, fine setae on each side, directed posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFCB0ECB0FBDBFB11" box="[861,1044,1164,1189]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Figs. 7, 8, 9, 11</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus long, ending in 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFAB9ECB1FAADFB11" box="[1364,1378,1165,1189]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
long tubes, ejaculatory apodeme thin and long, not expanded apically (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFC9BEC8CFC05FB7C" box="[886,970,1200,1225]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFC46EC8CFC05FB7C" box="[939,970,1200,1224]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AECE8FE3BFAEC" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Female terminalia. Ovipositor compressed, formed by segment VIII and the following (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFB42ECE8FAF5FB59" box="[1199,1338,1236,1261]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1373,193,1840]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 18. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Female. 14, Habitus, lateral view; 15, Ovipositor, lateral view; 16, Ovipositor, dorsal view; 17, Ovipositor, ventral view; 18, Genital fork and spermathecae. Abbreviations: ar: arms of genital fork; cap duct: capsular ducts; com duct: common duct; exp duct: expulsory ducts; cerc: cercus; f apod: furcal apodeme; spmth: spermathecae; stVIII: sternite VIII; tVII: tergite VII; tVIII: tergite VIII; tIX + X: tergite IX + X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFB1DECE9FAF5FB59" box="[1264,1338,1237,1261]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="15.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="14.0">14–17</number>
</figureCitation>
); genital fork with long, thin arms, about 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFDE1ECC4FDE0FAA5" box="[524,559,1272,1297]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times longer than base, base much wider than arms (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFB79ECC4FB25FAA4" box="[1172,1258,1272,1297]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1373,193,1840]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 18. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Female. 14, Habitus, lateral view; 15, Ovipositor, lateral view; 16, Ovipositor, dorsal view; 17, Ovipositor, ventral view; 18, Genital fork and spermathecae. Abbreviations: ar: arms of genital fork; cap duct: capsular ducts; com duct: common duct; exp duct: expulsory ducts; cerc: cercus; f apod: furcal apodeme; spmth: spermathecae; stVIII: sternite VIII; tVII: tergite VII; tVIII: tergite VIII; tIX + X: tergite IX + X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFB26ECC4FB25FAA4" box="[1227,1258,1272,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
); common duct long (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFF31ED20FEFCFA81" box="[220,307,1308,1333]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1373,193,1840]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 18. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Female. 14, Habitus, lateral view; 15, Ovipositor, lateral view; 16, Ovipositor, dorsal view; 17, Ovipositor, ventral view; 18, Genital fork and spermathecae. Abbreviations: ar: arms of genital fork; cap duct: capsular ducts; com duct: common duct; exp duct: expulsory ducts; cerc: cercus; f apod: furcal apodeme; spmth: spermathecae; stVIII: sternite VIII; tVII: tergite VII; tVIII: tergite VIII; tIX + X: tergite IX + X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFEF9ED21FEFCFA81" box="[276,307,1309,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFEA1ED21FE95FA81" box="[332,346,1309,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
expulsory and capsular ducts ending in 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFCD5ED21FC89FA81" box="[824,838,1309,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
spherical capsules, as wide as the width tip of the apodeme of the furca (
<figureCitation id="136B2A20FFAB5A1AFE7EED7CFE28FAEC" box="[403,487,1344,1369]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1373,193,1840]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 18. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Female. 14, Habitus, lateral view; 15, Ovipositor, lateral view; 16, Ovipositor, dorsal view; 17, Ovipositor, ventral view; 18, Genital fork and spermathecae. Abbreviations: ar: arms of genital fork; cap duct: capsular ducts; com duct: common duct; exp duct: expulsory ducts; cerc: cercus; f apod: furcal apodeme; spmth: spermathecae; stVIII: sternite VIII; tVII: tergite VII; tVIII: tergite VIII; tIX + X: tergite IX + X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFE25ED7CFE28FAEC" box="[456,487,1344,1368]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A652EFFAB5A1AFF2AED58FEE8F899" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AED58FF24F975" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFF2AED58FE83FAC9" bold="true" box="[199,332,1380,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Discussion.</emphasis>
In Papavero 
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFE15ED59FDF7FAC8" box="[504,568,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFDA2ED59FD43FAC9" box="[591,652,1381,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2009.0">2009</number>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D26FFAB5A1AFD4AED58FCF5FAC8" box="[679,826,1380,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Papaverellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFD4AED58FCF5FAC8" box="[679,826,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Papaverellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21757CCFFAB5A1AFCA4ED58FC75FAC9" box="[841,954,1380,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFCA4ED58FC75FAC9" bold="true" box="[841,954,1380,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, keys to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D26FFAB5A1AFBDAED58FA57FAC9" authority="Papavero, 2009" authorityName="Papavero" authorityYear="2009" box="[1079,1432,1380,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Scarbroughia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFBDAED58FB1FFAC8" box="[1079,1232,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Scarbroughia</emphasis>
Papavero, 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFAB1ED59FA57FAC9" box="[1372,1432,1381,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D26FFAB5A1AFEFFEDB4FE6AFA14" box="[274,421,1416,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Papaverellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFEFFEDB4FE6AFA14" box="[274,421,1416,1440]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Papaverellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21757CCFFAB5A1AFE5EEDB4FDECFA15" box="[435,547,1416,1441]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFE5EEDB4FDECFA15" bold="true" box="[435,547,1416,1441]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from it by the following characters: stylus 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFB74EDB4FB6CFA15" box="[1177,1187,1416,1441]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
½ times longer than postpedicel; 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFEC7ED91FEF7FA71" box="[298,312,1453,1477]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
apical scutellar macrosetae; setae present only in the fore and middle coxae, and sparse black macrosetae on the femora, tibiae and tarsi; basal 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFD56EDECFD0AFA5C" box="[699,709,1488,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFD22EDECFD10FA5C" box="[719,735,1488,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
of epandrium globose; hypandrium with abundant macrosetae and setae laterally; aedeagus with 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFDF6EDC9FDE6F9B9" box="[539,553,1525,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
very long, pointed prongs. By contrast, 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D26FFAB5A1AFC19EDC8FB42F9B8" box="[1012,1165,1524,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Scarbroughia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB7FFAB5A1AFC19EDC8FB42F9B8" box="[1012,1165,1524,1548]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Scarbroughia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has postpedicel as long as the scape and pedicel combined and as long as the stylus; 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFCD7EE24FC87F984" box="[826,840,1560,1584]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
or more apical scutellar macrosetae; apical 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFADCEE24FAF4F984" box="[1329,1339,1560,1584]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFAABEE24FA99F984" box="[1350,1366,1560,1584]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
of the fore and middle femora medially with stout bristles, all tibiae and tarsi, and coxae (mainly fore and middle ones) have long white macrosetae, in addition to more or less long, white, dense, appressed short setae; epandrium narrow, elongate; hypandrium with patches of short, sparse macrosetae lateroventrally; aedeagus with 
<number id="3D982482FFAB5A1AFABDEEB9FA91F929" box="[1360,1374,1669,1693]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
long prongs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A5FFAB5A1AFF2AEEF0FEE8F899" blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
